docs.lead_paragraph: A woman’s death in Nevada in October placed attention on the growing practice of full-body cryotherapy, which its enthusiasts say has many benefits.

headline.main: Claims for Cryotherapy Treatment Get New Scrutiny After a Death
headline.print_headline: Death in a Cryotherapy Tank Casts a Critical Light on Safety

docs.abstract: Death of Rejuvenice spa employee Chelsea Ake-Salvacion in cryotherapy chamber in Nevada has focused attention on quickly-growing but relatively unknown practice of full-body cryotherapy;  proponents call chambers safe, but her death has many questioning procedure's safety and claims of its supporters and Nevada officials have launched investigation; Food and Drug Administration does not recognize benefits of cryotherapy chambers and does not regulate devices.
docs.snippet: A woman’s death in Nevada in October placed attention on the growing practice of full-body cryotherapy, which its enthusiasts say has many benefits.
